Text.Value: As the steeple knows the arch, and the keystone knows the clay, I know you, for we are both parts of the same design.
We restored the spirit of the land around Moonrise. Nature is healing, and the tower can yet be restored to glory.
What greater good did you sell your soul for?
Pacts have great value. If yours did not, you were careless in making it.
I know you nonetheless. Not by name, not by reputation.
I'm looking for the Orphic Hammer.
Who are you?
The devil was true to his word. Fiends slaughtered my master's forces, but he endured somehow, and blighted the land.
You know my work? I am glad that it endures. Perhaps you also have the misfortune of knowing my master - general Ketheric Thorm.
Yes, I already have what I needed from Raphael.
I did not think it possible. Thank you - my spirit smiles for the first time in a century.
Who was your master?
I was an architect in life, a builder of tombs and temples, but mostly of towers. My proudest work reached for the stars and sought to dry Sel√ªne's tears.
It was a monument to life and to virtue, and a happy home to my master for many years.
We healed the land and lifted the shadow curse. Moonrise will be a beacon of light again.
I don't have time for this. I came here to find the Orphic Hammer.
I wish I could say it were not so.
Do you know Hope? I spoke to her a moment ago.
Moonrise is an affront to nature. It should be destroyed.
I know you.
I need to find my contract to break the deal I made.
The curse is no more, but Moonrise is tainted. It would be best reduced to rubble.
Not quite. Ketheric Thorm is dead, by my hand.
A great general, a greater man. Ketheric Thorm.
Perhaps it will fade into a long night and be forgotten, as I have. Perhaps that is for the best.
He marshalled a great army to ruin the world and bring all into shadow. I could not let it happen.
Dealing with devils never ends well.
But beware, the House is architecturally unstable. Left is sometimes right, but more often it is wrong.
Just as the moon wanes, Sel√ªne's blessings always fade.
Finish what business brought you here as quickly as possible, and then leave. Otherwise, you will be lost, like the rest of us.
You linger here still? Or perhaps you have become lost, like the rest of us.
And yet here you are, having made the same mistake. Find your contract, and undo it if you can.
It is easy to look for a thing. It is impossible to take it.
There is a stamp on your soul, as distinct as a mason's mark. Raphael owns you, just as he owns me.
Despite appearances, this whole House is more of a prison than a parlour. Most here have no choice but to remain.
When tragedy came, my master fell into darkness and despair.
Leave.
Deaths in the family. Happiness rarely lasts a lifetime.
A life with Our Lady of Silver is a good life.
Tell me what you know.
I sought out the devil Raphael and signed an infernal pact with him. He promised to destroy my master's army, and I promised him my soul in return.
A builder. A creator. A saviour.
Another sorry soul come to wander these halls. What do you seek?
Leave.
Tell me about the deal you signed.
I don't have time for this - I came here to find my contract.
Your actions may have justified the price of my soul. I thank you.
Moonrise is a cursed place - your legacy is in ruins.
You may be right, but those who live in desperate times often reach for desperate solutions. Be sure not to do the same.
I cannot help you. This is not my home, even if I can never leave.
By my oath, I did what the fiends could not, and vanquished Ketheric Thorm.
I need to find the Archive.
But at my foundation, I am a lost soul. We share that foundation.
How do you know about my deal?
Ketheric is no more. I killed him.
Now, go. Finish your business here, and leave while you can.
She will find you when you need her. That is Hope's way.
Now go, find your contract and save your soul.
All towers fall in the end. Thorm is vanquished - that was my purpose.
What went wrong?
Perhaps it is best that I remain here, and that the long centuries erode my memories and leave me empty. There is a certain peace in that.
Then my pact, the loss of my eternal soul... it was all for nothing.
Tell me what you know of this place.
Perhaps you should seek out the Archive...
My soul hangs in the balance - that's all I care about.
What ties you to the House of Hope?
Unless I'm mistaken, we've never met.
Leave.
It was a good life. I only wish our Lady had not averted her gaze from us.
Tell me - what became of my pride? What became of Moonrise Towers?
Dealing with devils rarely ends well - I speak from extensive experience.
Can you be sure that breaking the deal will do more good than harm?
Alas, it was a good that never came to be.
I'm not leaving until I find my contract.
Then all came to pass as I had hoped, though a century too late for my family and friends.
I am one such. This is not my home, but I can never leave.
This is a familiar tale. Are you the architect of Moonrise Towers?
Your intervention pushed Ketheric deeper into darkness. He became a Chosen of Myrkul.
No. I made the deal to help save Baldur's Gate.
Then I hope you find your contract and free yourself, but I fear for you. This is a dangerous place.
Then perhaps the greater good would be to leave this House, and to abide by the terms of your deal.
Like me, you made a deal with the devil, and authored your own damnable fate for the greater good.
Those who live in desperate times often reach for desperate solutions. I fear we have both lived in such times, but there is still hope for you.
Who was your master?
Sadly, the curse still grips the tower, and the lands around it.
Perhaps one day, new life will find it. Thank you.
You are right to hurry. My sorrows will only burden you.
Whatever mistakes you have made in the past, your deal with Raphael can still be undone. Find your contract, and then leave while you can.
The tower still stands, but it is a hollow place now.

Synopsis:
It's another debtor that players can meet in Feast Hall. 
He is the reference to a character that was mentioned in Act 2, Mason

Currently he's placed in the Feast Hall (as it will only win from adding another character), and it makes sense for him to clean the surrounding mess.
